    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-10-18T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-10-18T03:00:00-05:00" n="154"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d154">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">493.9283/10–1851: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Thailand</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Turner</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bangkok</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-10-18T15:00:00+07:00"
                            >October 18, 1951—3 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>913. Re <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 821, October 9, rptd Rangoon
                        334.<note n="1" xml:id="d154fn1">In telegram 821 to Bangkok, October 9, the
                        Embassy was asked to confirm reports that the smuggling of arms and
                        equipment to the <gloss target="#t_KMT1">KMT</gloss> troops in Burma had
                        ceased. The Embassy in Rangoon had initiated this request in order to pass
                        this information along to the Burmese Foreign Office if these reports were
                        true. (493.9283/9–1951)</note>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss> confirmed to me today reports
                    mentioned <gloss target="#t_reftel1">reftel</gloss> that smuggling arms thru
                    Thai to <gloss target="#t_KMT1">KMT</gloss> troops Burma has already ceased. He
                    stated that Thai Govt had issued strict instructions to Min Interior<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d154fn2">Lt. Gen. Mangkorn Phrom Yodhi.</note> to prevent such
                    smuggling, and that he expected be able give me soon further details of measures
                    being taken in this direction.</p>
                <p>Sent Dept 913, rptd Rangoon 934.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Turner</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
